  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nAnvil\r\n\r\n### Describe the feature you would like\r\n\r\nGiven that resetting in anvil can now start a fork (https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/pull/5834), it would be useful if anvil provided an RPC method that can change the chain ID, effectively allowing the same anvil instance to fork one chain after another programatically, without a restart. \r\n\r\nI'm currently working on some fork testing functionality in [CoW services](https://github.com/cowprotocol/services/) for which this feature would be useful, as we'll be able to test against multiple forked chains with different IDs without restarting anvil.\r\n\r\nPull request to enable this is here: https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/pull/6047",
